WEBVTT

00:46.880 --> 00:50.760
WOMAN GROANS

00:50.800 --> 00:52.837
WOMAN MOANS

00:59.760 --> 01:05.756
WOMAN GROANS AND SCREAMS

01:08.960 --> 01:11.110
Samira. Samira, quickly.

01:20.040 --> 01:21.394
WOMAN PANTS

01:21.440 --> 01:23.351
It won't come. It won't come.

01:31.000 --> 01:33.913
WOMAN SCREAMS

01:48.760 --> 01:53.311
KNIFE SLICES FLESH
<i>—</i> WOMAN SCREAMS

02:04.600 --> 02:12.600
BABY CRIES

02:22.360 --> 02:24.271
Look, Cassandra.

02:25.720 --> 02:27.313
You have a baby brother.

02:31.480 --> 02:33.551
CROWDS SCREAM

02:47.480 --> 02:49.994
Ya! Ya!

02:51.040 --> 02:53.953
Get them in there, Paris!
<i>—</i> Ya, ya!

02:59.080 --> 03:01.515
Cantenaus, move them!

03:01.560 --> 03:02.675
Come on!

03:30.400 --> 03:32.596
We need a woman around here.

03:32.640 --> 03:34.074
MEN CHUCKLE

03:38.080 --> 03:40.515
WOMAN LAUGHS

03:42.240 --> 03:43.310
<i>HE GROW LS</i>

03:43.360 --> 03:44.839
SHE SQUEALS

03:56.480 --> 03:59.757
AGELAUS:
Paris! Where are you?

03:59.800 --> 04:00.790
He's calling.

04:02.400 --> 04:03.390
AGELAUS:
Paris!

04:03.440 --> 04:05.272
His horses can wait.

04:05.320 --> 04:08.153
I've got a beast of my own
to take care of.

04:13.320 --> 04:14.913
Where have you been?

04:14.960 --> 04:17.600
I was... checking the fences.

04:19.760 --> 04:20.954
What happened?

04:21.000 --> 04:23.719
Bloody wolves scared them!

04:23.760 --> 04:25.433
Let's round them up, huh?

04:29.200 --> 04:30.190
Shit.

04:32.320 --> 04:33.594
Paris!

05:06.000 --> 05:07.832
HORSE WHINNIES

05:24.880 --> 05:28.191
DISTANT FEMALE LAUGHTER

05:32.200 --> 05:38.196
LAUGHTER CONTINUES

05:50.280 --> 05:53.432
Paris. Son of Agelaus the herdsman.

05:56.200 --> 05:57.395
Who wants to know?

05:58.960 --> 06:01.474
You've been chosen to resolve a dispute.

06:02.680 --> 06:06.514
Decide which of these
three goddesses is the finest.

06:06.720 --> 06:08.074
Goddesses?

06:08.120 --> 06:11.192
Whoever you choose
will receive the golden apple.

06:13.360 --> 06:15.192
I herd cows.

06:15.240 --> 06:17.880
How can I decide something like that?

06:17.920 --> 06:21.914
Zeus, bringer of storms,
selected you personally.

06:23.840 --> 06:24.830
Why me?

06:25.920 --> 06:26.910
It's just a game.

06:33.840 --> 06:35.990
But maybe we have the wrong person.

06:36.040 --> 06:38.509
No. We have the right person.

06:44.240 --> 06:45.514
Takeit

06:49.000 --> 06:49.910
As I thought.

06:59.520 --> 07:02.797
No good will come of this.
<i>—</i> Quiet, Hermes, you've said enough.

07:04.560 --> 07:05.550
Hera.

07:12.280 --> 07:14.078
Give me the apple, Paris...

07:18.240 --> 07:20.311
And I'll make you
the most powerful man alive.

07:20.360 --> 07:22.795
Don't listen to her.
<i>—</i> Athena.

07:27.960 --> 07:29.280
Choose me, Paris.

07:31.240 --> 07:33.516
With me by your side

07:33.560 --> 07:36.393
you'll be the most admired man on earth.

07:37.640 --> 07:39.278
You know me, of course...

07:41.520 --> 07:43.796
From your dreams.

07:43.840 --> 07:45.353
Aphrodite.

07:46.480 --> 07:47.550
Goddess of love.

07:51.120 --> 07:52.599
Grant me the apple...

07:54.040 --> 07:56.793
and I'll give you the most
beautiful woman in the world.

07:58.800 --> 08:00.120
Who is she?

08:00.160 --> 08:03.232
Hm! You'll know her when you see her.

08:05.400 --> 08:06.435
Time to decide.

08:08.720 --> 08:12.998
WHISPERING ETHEREAL VOICES

08:26.560 --> 08:27.755
I choose you.

08:28.800 --> 08:30.552
DISTANT THUNDER RUMBLES

08:47.480 --> 08:49.756
What have you done?!
<i>—</i> Enough!

08:50.880 --> 08:52.314
The mortal has spoken.

09:05.040 --> 09:07.031
COW MOOS

09:12.720 --> 09:15.280
Wait! When do I meet my prize?

09:52.200 --> 09:54.510
Why don't you marry her, huh?

09:55.560 --> 09:56.959
You won't find better.

10:13.800 --> 10:19.796
WHISPERING ETHEREAL VOICE

10:44.800 --> 10:45.790
Ya]

11:15.920 --> 11:17.069
Where are you?

11:32.280 --> 11:33.395
Keep your distance.

11:39.560 --> 11:40.550
Who are they?

11:42.480 --> 11:43.515
Them?

11:44.240 --> 11:45.435
None of your kind.

11:46.880 --> 11:48.200
What are they doing?

11:48.880 --> 11:51.315
Training. For the city games.

11:54.960 --> 11:55.950
Nice horse.

12:03.560 --> 12:06.359
Hey! What the hell are you doing?!

12:33.240 --> 12:34.196
Hey!

12:41.240 --> 12:43.197
Woohoo!

12:56.320 --> 12:57.310
Woo!

13:00.840 --> 13:03.673
You may be lords in the city.
But here I rule.

13:03.720 --> 13:05.552
We're not lords, friend.

13:05.600 --> 13:07.079
We're princes of Troy.

13:09.840 --> 13:11.239
Priam's sons.

13:11.800 --> 13:13.393
And you're out of your depth.

13:14.280 --> 13:15.759
No hard feelings.

13:15.800 --> 13:17.791
Just be more careful next time.

13:19.960 --> 13:21.075
Take me to the games.

13:23.440 --> 13:27.195
I'll bet my life I can beat any of you
at any event.

13:31.320 --> 13:33.357
I'll give you one chance
to take that back.

13:46.920 --> 13:50.470
DISTANT CROWD CHEERS

14:00.200 --> 14:03.238
CROWDS CHEER AND SHOUT

14:56.000 --> 14:57.354
You're next.

15:08.320 --> 15:11.472
My brother, Hector,
will fight you for our family's honour.

15:12.480 --> 15:15.120
Bow down or accept his challenge.

15:20.720 --> 15:21.790
Are you mad?

15:33.680 --> 15:34.750
Takeit

15:52.640 --> 15:55.280
CHEERS

16:04.520 --> 16:05.874
PARIS YELLS

16:13.760 --> 16:19.711
FIGHTING GRUNTS

17:18.520 --> 17:20.352
Hector, stop!

17:24.839 --> 17:26.273
Paris!

17:35.960 --> 17:37.109
Get up.

17:53.720 --> 17:54.710
PRIAM GASPS

17:56.000 --> 17:57.673
HECUBA GASPS

18:04.320 --> 18:05.879
A miracle has occurred.

18:08.800 --> 18:10.598
This boy is Alexander.

18:13.840 --> 18:14.989
Our son.

18:16.600 --> 18:18.159
The gods have saved his life!

18:19.840 --> 18:21.399
They've brought him back to us.

18:23.520 --> 18:26.638
CROWD CLAMOURS

18:52.960 --> 18:55.713
PARIS SHIVERS

19:11.960 --> 19:15.157
The blood ran black.
You can't do this.

19:16.080 --> 19:17.195
I beg you...

19:17.240 --> 19:20.278
I prayed for his return
every day for 20 years.

19:20.320 --> 19:23.119
We both did.
<i>—</i> My lord, please listen...

19:23.160 --> 19:24.309
We did listen to you.

19:24.960 --> 19:27.634
I won't suffer again like that, I won't.
<i>—</i> I know.

19:27.680 --> 19:30.320
You're making a great mistake.

19:30.360 --> 19:33.079
The gods do not forget.

19:35.680 --> 19:36.829
KNOCK AT DOOR

19:37.880 --> 19:39.029
SERVANT:
Your majesties.

19:40.920 --> 19:42.069
<i>Leave us, Utes.</i>

19:42.120 --> 19:43.599
We'll discuss this further
in the morning.

19:54.160 --> 19:55.389
Let me look at you.

20:01.760 --> 20:03.433
You must have a thousand questions.

20:05.760 --> 20:06.750
I'm a shepherd.

20:08.160 --> 20:10.151
I'm not good with words.

20:10.200 --> 20:12.237
You're not a shepherd any more.

20:13.160 --> 20:15.310
It's hard, I know.
But you must understand

20:15.360 --> 20:17.192
that Paris is not your name.

20:17.760 --> 20:21.754
And although he has shown
you great kindness...

20:21.800 --> 20:24.269
Agelaus is not your father.

20:24.320 --> 20:27.631
Your name is Alexander, Prince of Troy.

20:29.680 --> 20:34.197
You were taken by wolves from this window
when you were three days old.

20:35.920 --> 20:38.719
Agelaus found you on the mountain track

20:38.760 --> 20:40.797
where the wolves left you.

20:40.840 --> 20:43.753
I found you wrapped
in a parcel of cloth.

20:45.400 --> 20:47.073
I named you Paris.

20:47.120 --> 20:48.952
It's a miracle you survived.

20:50.840 --> 20:52.319
I thought you were dead.

20:55.560 --> 20:58.029
PRIAM:
Agelaus, thank you.

20:58.080 --> 21:00.390
The city owes you a great debt.

21:00.440 --> 21:03.751
Now, please, say goodbye to my son.

21:15.400 --> 21:16.390
Father.

21:27.640 --> 21:29.074
Goodbye, Alexander.

21:40.080 --> 21:42.799
Come. Come here.

21:49.880 --> 21:51.473
I've missed you so much.

22:07.240 --> 22:08.560
To your new family!

22:08.600 --> 22:10.796
CROWD CHEERS

22:23.920 --> 22:24.990
Come here.

22:31.640 --> 22:34.678
CROWD NOISE FADES

22:47.920 --> 22:51.914
BABY CRIES

23:01.560 --> 23:03.039
<i>CASSANDRA GASPS</i>

23:05.560 --> 23:08.393
What have you given to calm her?
<i>—</i> She refuses to drink anything.

23:08.440 --> 23:10.750
She hasn't been like this in years.

23:14.640 --> 23:16.950
Cassandra? I'm here.

23:17.000 --> 23:19.230
Mother...
<i>—</i> It's all right, Cassandra.

23:19.280 --> 23:23.274
The new prince... I see it in his eyes.

23:23.320 --> 23:24.310
Black blood!

23:26.280 --> 23:27.554
Shh.

23:27.600 --> 23:28.999
Don't let him back.

23:29.040 --> 23:30.314
Don't let him back.

23:34.600 --> 23:36.750
It's alright, my love.

23:36.800 --> 23:37.790
It's alright.

23:40.760 --> 23:41.750
There.

23:43.120 --> 23:45.509
Give her what she needs.
<i>—</i> Yes, my lady.

23:45.880 --> 23:47.359
Shh.

23:49.760 --> 23:50.955
Close the windows.

23:56.280 --> 23:58.396
WOMAN SOBS

24:02.720 --> 24:04.757
WOMAN:
Please. Please!

24:06.160 --> 24:08.754
MY baby, please, no!

24:09.960 --> 24:12.759
No! Please, mY babY!

24:43.640 --> 24:46.598
UPBEAT FLUTE MUSIC

24:54.080 --> 24:56.390
PARIS YELLS

25:00.120 --> 25:01.793
WOMAN:
Come on, up you get!

25:01.840 --> 25:03.672
Let me try one more time!

25:11.280 --> 25:13.920
PARIS GROANS

25:46.240 --> 25:47.560
SOLDIER 1:
Get out!

25:48.280 --> 25:49.429
SOLDIER 2:
Don't come back!

26:00.560 --> 26:01.789
Come on, Cassandra.

26:03.840 --> 26:05.035
Come on.

26:05.080 --> 26:08.596
Our sister, Cassandra,
why doesn't she come to meals?

26:08.640 --> 26:09.960
Cassandra is unwell.

26:11.240 --> 26:12.674
Can't I at least meet her?

26:12.720 --> 26:14.597
You focus on your own behaviour
and leave her to us.

26:14.640 --> 26:15.994
My behaviour?

26:16.960 --> 26:19.156
I'm sorry if I'm a disappointment
to you all.

26:19.200 --> 26:20.713
No, you're not.

26:22.720 --> 26:24.313
But the party's over.

26:25.160 --> 26:28.073
No more visits to the lower city.
No more late nights.

26:28.120 --> 26:29.440
It's time for work.

26:29.480 --> 26:31.471
I thought princes didn't work.

26:32.680 --> 26:34.318
I thought that was the point.

26:35.200 --> 26:38.397
Well, they don't herd cows,
if that's what you mean.

26:38.440 --> 26:41.637
Maybe you should just send me back.
<i>—</i> No one's sending you back.

26:41.680 --> 26:43.990
And no—one's asking you
to change who you are.

26:45.800 --> 26:46.790
Pandarus.

26:50.640 --> 26:52.358
My lord?
<i>—</i> What's this?

26:53.000 --> 26:55.230
Your first official engagement.

26:56.320 --> 26:58.311
I have a friend across the waters.

26:58.360 --> 27:00.556
King Menelaus of Sparta.
<i>—</i> Father...

27:00.600 --> 27:03.035
I want you to represent me.

27:03.080 --> 27:06.118
Pandarus will go with you.
Introduce yourself, pay tribute.

27:07.040 --> 27:08.633
The rediscovered son.

27:09.480 --> 27:11.790
Strengthen the ties between
our two lands.

27:11.840 --> 27:15.071
And how exactly do I do that?
<i>—</i> Well, you'll learn.

27:18.000 --> 27:19.911
Prove yourself a prince, son.

27:22.680 --> 27:23.829
Well then.

27:24.880 --> 27:26.075
Better get dressed.

27:36.360 --> 27:38.510
He's not ready.
<i>—</i> Let me go with him.

27:38.560 --> 27:40.039
No. He'll learn on his own.

27:59.600 --> 28:01.159
If this is work...

28:02.680 --> 28:03.670
let me work.

28:09.680 --> 28:11.034
Land ahead!

28:46.680 --> 28:48.910
Your quarters
are in the south of the palace

28:48.960 --> 28:51.759
and afford the finest views
of the region.

28:56.520 --> 28:58.431
Tonight, the king will hold a banquet

28:58.480 --> 29:00.471
in honour of Prince Alexander.

29:02.800 --> 29:04.393
You should sleep now.

29:05.400 --> 29:07.232
You need to be on form tonight.

29:51.280 --> 29:52.270
My lord.

30:00.960 --> 30:04.555
We bring you... oil of iris

30:04.600 --> 30:07.069
frankincense, rose and musk

30:07.120 --> 30:13.116
spices from the east, cumin and...

30:13.160 --> 30:14.992
PANDARUS WHISPERS: Turmeric.
<i>—</i> ...turmeric.

30:15.640 --> 30:19.190
From Africa, boxes of ebony.
Ostrich eggs.

30:19.240 --> 30:21.993
All of Troy's traders
pay tribute to King Menelaus.

30:22.040 --> 30:24.395
They bring the world to Sparta.

30:26.360 --> 30:29.557
Let us feast to celebrate
the new Prince of Troy.

30:39.400 --> 30:40.959
The queen not joining us?

30:43.000 --> 30:44.115
Helen's unwell tonight.

30:45.640 --> 30:46.789
I'm sorry to hear that.

30:46.840 --> 30:48.353
She will feast when she recovers.

30:50.440 --> 30:53.159
So, your story is a strange one.

30:55.600 --> 30:58.319
I should like to hear it
from your mouth.

30:59.960 --> 31:01.871
It was a miracle of the gods.

31:03.200 --> 31:05.237
I was stolen from a palace...
<i>—</i> DOOR OPENS

31:07.960 --> 31:13.034
BIRDS SING

31:26.160 --> 31:27.639
I'm sorry. I'm late.

31:30.240 --> 31:32.629
My darling, you are recovered.

31:33.840 --> 31:36.400
Curiosity defeated my tiredness.

31:36.440 --> 31:38.954
Sit. Save your strength.

31:45.680 --> 31:50.311
I was just asking Prince Alexander here
to recount his charming story.

31:51.160 --> 31:53.390
Are those your birds, my lady?
<i>—</i> Yes.

31:55.480 --> 31:57.471
My father always let them
fly free in the house.

31:58.280 --> 32:00.271
One of his little indulgences.

32:02.760 --> 32:04.353
I interrupted you, my lord.

32:04.800 --> 32:06.996
<i>—</i> Please.

32:09.520 --> 32:12.512
I was stolen from the palace window
as a baby by wolves.

32:13.600 --> 32:17.434
This shepherd found me on the mountain
and took me into his house.

32:17.480 --> 32:19.596
Unaware of your true nature.

32:19.960 --> 32:21.189
Yes.

32:22.280 --> 32:24.032
He called me Paris.

32:24.080 --> 32:26.754
He taught me to ride and run cattle.

32:26.800 --> 32:28.438
For 20 years, that was my life.

32:28.480 --> 32:30.118
|\/|y lady.

32:30.160 --> 32:33.551
Then, a few weeks ago, I saw the princes
training on the plain.

32:33.600 --> 32:36.069
I challenged them.
<i>—</i> And you won?

32:36.120 --> 32:37.519
Yes.

32:37.560 --> 32:39.870
Until you fought your brother, Hector.

32:39.920 --> 32:40.910
Yes.

32:41.840 --> 32:43.160
He would have killed me.

32:43.200 --> 32:47.353
But my father recognised
me from a birthmark and I was spared.

32:47.400 --> 32:48.356
Show me.

32:54.720 --> 32:56.552
INDISTINCT WHISPERS IN CROWD

32:58.280 --> 33:00.954
To think something so small
could change so much.

33:08.040 --> 33:09.838
How did you two get together?

33:09.880 --> 33:10.836
PANDARUS CLEARS HIS THROAT

33:13.560 --> 33:15.233
No. No, it's fine.

33:16.880 --> 33:19.599
It's a good story and he should know it.

33:20.840 --> 33:22.877
My brother won Helen for me
in competition.

33:24.000 --> 33:26.594
He fought 100 lords for Sparta,

33:26.640 --> 33:28.039
and the right to Helen's hand.

33:28.840 --> 33:30.911
So you didn't win her yourself?

33:36.640 --> 33:38.472
Be careful, Prince.

33:39.840 --> 33:42.229
Your father wrote in his letters
you had much to learn.

33:45.680 --> 33:47.079
What else did he say?

33:48.200 --> 33:50.794
I can't read, so I wouldn't know.

33:50.840 --> 33:52.399
It's time for bed, I think.

33:52.440 --> 33:55.478
The queen must not
over-strain herself and you...

33:55.520 --> 33:58.319
you must be tired after
your long journey.

33:58.360 --> 34:00.556
Everyone keeps telling me
that I should be tired. But, er...

34:03.320 --> 34:04.276
I'm not.

34:04.320 --> 34:05.435
But the queen is.

34:16.040 --> 34:20.159
DISTANT MUSIC SOUNDS

34:31.960 --> 34:34.600
MAN SNORES

34:56.520 --> 34:59.353
WOMEN WHISPER AND GIGGLE

35:56.040 --> 35:58.270
The queen's women are beautiful.

36:00.920 --> 36:02.831
They've been friends of my wife's
since birth.

36:04.160 --> 36:05.992
You're a lucky man.

36:06.040 --> 36:07.030
You think so?

36:08.520 --> 36:09.840
I miss my real home.

36:11.280 --> 36:12.714
Have you been to Mycenae?

36:12.760 --> 36:14.034
No.

36:14.080 --> 36:15.559
You should.

36:15.600 --> 36:17.398
There we have real culture.

36:18.520 --> 36:20.238
This place is a wilderness.

36:20.760 --> 36:23.149
Though I've done my best to tame it.

36:24.800 --> 36:25.915
But look at her.

36:28.640 --> 36:29.710
She's worth it all.

36:30.800 --> 36:31.710
But we were saying...

36:33.040 --> 36:34.030
Helen.

36:42.200 --> 36:43.634
Bring our daughter to meet our guest.

36:45.560 --> 36:46.595
Hermione.

36:51.680 --> 36:53.159
Meet the Prince of Troy.

36:55.120 --> 36:56.918
Beautiful, isn't she?

36:57.840 --> 36:59.160
And with brains to match.

37:01.160 --> 37:02.798
You may go now, Hermione.

37:04.080 --> 37:05.070
No, wait.

37:05.880 --> 37:07.632
Hermione will need a husband soon.

37:09.040 --> 37:12.556
Dynastic marriages strengthen
all parties involved.

37:12.600 --> 37:15.718
They are like hands held fast
across the water.

37:18.480 --> 37:20.915
That's the reason your
father sent you here, Prince.

37:22.800 --> 37:24.279
Or didn't you know?

37:27.080 --> 37:28.559
I'm honoured to be
considered worthy of her.

37:30.000 --> 37:32.037
I didn't say you were.
<i>—</i> Ah.

37:32.720 --> 37:33.710
Not yet.

37:36.320 --> 37:37.435
Come, Hermione.

37:41.240 --> 37:43.993
We should find time to discuss
that other matter, Pandarus.

37:44.040 --> 37:45.838
Whenever you wish, my lord.

37:50.800 --> 37:52.199
Did you know about this?

37:52.240 --> 37:53.435
Why?

37:54.520 --> 37:55.590
Doesn't it please you?

37:55.640 --> 37:56.869
Of course it does.

37:57.760 --> 37:59.398
If it's my father's wish.

38:00.840 --> 38:01.796
And yours.

38:02.320 --> 38:03.469
It's business.

38:05.680 --> 38:07.671
My husband wants a treaty with Troy.

38:08.560 --> 38:10.676
My daughter is part of the deal.

38:10.720 --> 38:13.109
Is Troy that important?

38:13.160 --> 38:15.037
Troy controls the straits from Asia.

38:16.240 --> 38:18.117
Everything passes through your city.

38:19.160 --> 38:21.549
Tin from the east to make bronze.

38:22.520 --> 38:24.238
Spices from India.

38:26.880 --> 38:28.598
So everyone wants a piece.

38:29.520 --> 38:31.716
Welcome to the world, Prince.

38:37.560 --> 38:39.358
Why do you look at me like that?

38:40.160 --> 38:42.390
Surprised I have a mind of my own?

38:44.680 --> 38:46.717
Not surprised in the slightest.

38:48.760 --> 38:49.955
How did you sleep?

38:57.600 --> 38:58.829
Not so well.

39:01.280 --> 39:03.476
In Troy, we've got the sea breeze.

39:03.520 --> 39:04.999
Cools the skin.

39:05.040 --> 39:06.269
Here...

39:07.920 --> 39:09.354
the heat's like a furnace.

39:13.600 --> 39:15.796
And then I thought I heard music.

39:17.080 --> 39:18.878
But maybe I was wrong.

39:28.000 --> 39:30.037
Do you know the story of Actaeon?

39:31.720 --> 39:32.790
No.

39:34.160 --> 39:35.195
Should I?

39:36.840 --> 39:40.196
He spied on the bathing goddess Diana

39:41.360 --> 39:44.193
and was turned into a stag
for his pains.

39:46.360 --> 39:48.795
Dogs chased him through the forest...

39:51.440 --> 39:53.477
and tore his flesh to pieces.

39:57.360 --> 39:59.271
Maybe it was worth it.

40:08.840 --> 40:10.353
PRIAM:
They're staying longer.

40:11.280 --> 40:15.751
Pandarus thinks that Menelaus
will agree to the marriage to his daughter.

40:15.800 --> 40:17.632
I don't like him being away.

40:18.200 --> 40:20.157
He's reckless.

40:20.200 --> 40:22.111
Well, I was reckless at his age

40:22.160 --> 40:23.480
or I'd never have won you.

40:26.520 --> 40:28.750
The gods have forgiven us, Hecuba.

40:30.200 --> 40:31.599
WhY Can't you?

40:33.120 --> 40:36.158
Odysseus of Ithaca sends his
greatest tributes and affections

40:36.200 --> 40:38.760
along with the finest alabaster
from Assyria

40:38.800 --> 40:42.680
Iapis lazuli from Bactra
and jasper from Minoa.

40:42.720 --> 40:47.715
All of Troy is grateful and pays tribute
to the great King Odysseus.

40:52.360 --> 40:55.990
King Agamemnon of Mycenae
sends his respects

40:56.040 --> 40:58.554
and, along with it, a chariot of gold.

41:00.120 --> 41:03.158
King Agamemnon
won the beauteous Helen

41:03.200 --> 41:05.476
and the kingdom of Sparta
for his brother.

41:05.520 --> 41:08.034
He knows the true value of a gem.

41:20.680 --> 41:24.071
May I walk with your daughter, my lord?

41:24.120 --> 41:25.952
It's only right we get to know each other.

41:29.680 --> 41:30.715
Of course.

41:31.560 --> 41:32.959
Hermione.

41:33.000 --> 41:34.957
Show the prince the chamber of silks.

41:47.560 --> 41:49.949
These were a gift from an Indian king.

41:51.680 --> 41:54.035
He tried to buy my mother's hand, but...

41:54.080 --> 41:55.434
she turned him down.

41:56.320 --> 41:57.355
Why?

41:58.880 --> 42:02.111
She refused all offers until her father
forced her to take a husband.

42:02.160 --> 42:03.798
Didn't she want to marry?

42:05.400 --> 42:07.391
Must we always talk about her?

42:10.320 --> 42:12.357
What do you want to talk about?

42:14.320 --> 42:15.549
I don't know.

42:17.040 --> 42:20.237
I'm not sure what to say or do.

42:21.880 --> 42:25.874
I'm not like my mother,
I'm not skilled in these things.

42:29.400 --> 42:30.834
I'm not good with men.

42:32.840 --> 42:34.433
I don't know what to do.

42:35.920 --> 42:36.910
It's alright.

42:38.480 --> 42:39.470
It's alright.

42:50.120 --> 42:51.918
Hermione.

42:51.960 --> 42:54.110
Your father wants to see you.

42:54.160 --> 42:55.798
He asked me to come here.

42:57.400 --> 42:59.471
He didn't ask you
to make a fool of yourself.

43:00.440 --> 43:02.397
I'll show the prince the silks myself.

43:13.440 --> 43:14.714
Stop playing games.

43:17.040 --> 43:18.030
Games, my lady?

43:19.360 --> 43:21.192
It may suit my husband to do so.

43:21.240 --> 43:23.197
It does not suit you.

43:23.240 --> 43:25.550
Hermione's a girl.
She's not ready for courtship.

43:25.600 --> 43:27.113
I wasn't courting her.

43:27.840 --> 43:29.831
I was comforting her.

43:29.880 --> 43:31.154
That's not what it looked like.

43:31.200 --> 43:33.032
Well, that's what it was.

43:34.280 --> 43:36.954
We should go back to the dinner.
<i>—</i> Not yet.

43:37.000 --> 43:39.913
All those bloody dinners.
They're stifling.

43:46.120 --> 43:48.919
These silks were given to my father...

43:48.960 --> 43:50.792
BOTH:
...by an Indian king.

43:50.840 --> 43:52.160
You turned him down.

43:53.200 --> 43:55.476
I know.
<i>—</i> Then there's nothing more to say.

43:56.520 --> 43:57.510
We should go.

44:00.400 --> 44:02.038
Please don't look at me like that.

44:03.040 --> 44:05.236
I'm your hostess
and queen of this palace.

44:05.280 --> 44:06.759
And does that make you happy?

44:07.600 --> 44:09.352
It's no concern of yours how I feel.

44:11.440 --> 44:16.071
I bet this palace was once very different
when it was yours and your father's.

44:17.120 --> 44:18.519
And you were different, too.

44:20.360 --> 44:21.794
What do you mean?

44:21.840 --> 44:25.037
Your world here was wild.

44:25.080 --> 44:26.878
Your civilised husband didn't want that.

44:26.920 --> 44:28.957
It scared him. So he tamed it.

44:29.000 --> 44:30.354
And he tamed you, too.

44:30.840 --> 44:33.434
I'm a woman.
We don't get to select our fate.

44:33.480 --> 44:34.470
What fate?!

44:35.880 --> 44:38.554
A life of gritting your teeth
through banquets?

44:38.600 --> 44:40.352
Drugging yourself into oblivion?

44:41.160 --> 44:43.515
<i>I know</i> what freedom is.

44:43.560 --> 44:45.836
And this... this isn't it.

44:48.040 --> 44:49.269
You're royal now.

44:50.280 --> 44:53.352
Duty will be your master, too.
— No one can master me.

44:57.840 --> 44:58.955
Except maybe you.

45:00.240 --> 45:01.958
Be careful what you say.

45:04.200 --> 45:06.350
Caution never got me anywhere.

45:07.400 --> 45:09.357
What gives you the right?

45:11.880 --> 45:12.870
The gods.

45:17.240 --> 45:18.230
Please don't.

45:20.880 --> 45:22.757
Are you happy?

45:22.800 --> 45:24.154
Tell me yes and I'll go.

45:24.200 --> 45:26.510
I'll marry your daughter,
just as they all want.

45:30.200 --> 45:31.918
POUNDING ON DOOR

45:35.360 --> 45:38.671
POUNDING CONTINUES

45:38.720 --> 45:39.710
MAN:
Open up!

45:41.920 --> 45:43.240
What is it?

45:43.280 --> 45:45.510
My lady, I come from Mycenae.

45:45.560 --> 45:47.278
The king's father is dead.

45:54.720 --> 45:56.154
Your father.

46:04.360 --> 46:06.271
My brother's set sail for Crete.

46:06.920 --> 46:08.115
I'm to join him there for the funeral.

46:08.160 --> 46:11.869
I'll come with you.
<i>—</i> No, we have a guest. You stay.

46:11.920 --> 46:14.594
My lord, if it's easier for us to leave,
just say.

46:14.640 --> 46:17.473
I'll not hear it.
My father has been sick for some time.

46:17.520 --> 46:19.033
His death was not unexpected.

46:20.000 --> 46:21.559
But we must look to the future.

46:22.640 --> 46:23.960
Celebrate new alliances.

46:28.320 --> 46:30.960
You have spirit, Alexander.
I admire that.

46:33.040 --> 46:35.031
Please, stay.

46:36.360 --> 46:37.759
Get to know Hermione.

46:40.160 --> 46:41.150
Come, Helen.

46:54.360 --> 46:55.316
Five days.

