48:56.880 --> 48:58.871
Why do you stare at her chair?

49:03.200 --> 49:04.190
Men are fools.

49:10.120 --> 49:12.760
My lord!
<i>—</i> Pack the bags. We're leaving.

49:12.800 --> 49:15.838
His highness asked...
<i>—</i> I don't care what he asked!

49:15.880 --> 49:17.234
THUNDER CLAPS

49:17.280 --> 49:18.953
A storm is coming.
We must wait till morning.

49:19.000 --> 49:20.593
No, we're leaving now!

49:22.840 --> 49:25.434
My lord! My um!

49:27.120 --> 49:29.031
We must wait till morning!

49:35.560 --> 49:37.915
PANDARUS:
Get these carts loaded! Quickly!

49:37.960 --> 49:39.473
MAN: Yes, sir.

49:41.880 --> 49:43.678
Come on!

49:45.120 --> 49:46.269
Get these loaded.

49:49.840 --> 49:51.558
Get these loaded, come on.

49:59.160 --> 50:00.559
HE SCREAMS

50:06.360 --> 50:07.350
KNOCK AT DOOR

51:06.760 --> 51:08.319
Why didn't you leave?

51:11.440 --> 51:12.555
I tried.

51:21.480 --> 51:22.993
The gods didn't let me.

51:27.720 --> 51:29.358
I tried to hide from you.

51:31.760 --> 51:32.875
I locked my door.

51:35.840 --> 51:36.955
I couldn't sleep.

51:40.480 --> 51:41.993
Three clays in darkness.

51:44.800 --> 51:45.835
I've gone mad.

51:47.600 --> 51:48.829
You've made me mad.

52:08.840 --> 52:12.913
THUNDER RUMBLES

53:03.840 --> 53:05.194
What?

53:09.560 --> 53:11.597
I was thinking about your name.

53:13.280 --> 53:14.350
Paris.

53:17.800 --> 53:18.790
I like it.

53:20.840 --> 53:21.955
It suits you better.

53:39.000 --> 53:40.479
There's something I haven't told you.

53:43.320 --> 53:44.913
When I was a shepherd...

53:48.160 --> 53:52.836
I was told by Aphrodite I'd meet
the world's most beautiful woman...

53:54.520 --> 53:57.512
and that she'd be mine.

53:59.360 --> 54:00.839
And you think that's me?

54:00.880 --> 54:01.870
I'm sure of it.

54:02.720 --> 54:03.710
You're a fool.

54:09.040 --> 54:12.590
PANDARUS:
My lord! My lord!

54:14.640 --> 54:16.950
PANDARUS:
Prince Alexander!

54:18.920 --> 54:19.830
MY lord!

54:22.280 --> 54:24.078
Your men are calling.

54:24.120 --> 54:25.155
PANDARUS:
My lord!

54:31.520 --> 54:32.840
You should go.

54:32.880 --> 54:34.279
I can't leave you.

54:36.560 --> 54:38.995
They can't find you here.
My husband will have you killed.

54:39.840 --> 54:41.114
When will I see you again?

54:42.080 --> 54:43.070
I don't know.

54:43.880 --> 54:45.200
Maybe at your wedding to my daughter.

54:45.240 --> 54:47.516
That will never happen.
<i>—</i> Well, then, never.

54:51.240 --> 54:53.629
Just go. Please.
<i>—</i> Come with me.

54:56.680 --> 54:58.273
I can't.

54:58.320 --> 55:01.358
Come now,
before your husband gets back.

55:01.400 --> 55:03.676
It's impossible. I'd be seen.
People would know.

55:03.720 --> 55:06.075
You say that you are a woman
and that you have no choice in life.

55:06.120 --> 55:08.396
But that's not true.
You have a choice now.

55:08.440 --> 55:09.919
I have a daughter.

55:11.440 --> 55:13.078
I can't just walk away.

55:14.400 --> 55:16.755
She doesn't deserve that.
<i>—</i> And what about you?

55:20.040 --> 55:21.474
What do you deserve?

55:33.680 --> 55:37.275
Please, just... just go!

55:49.440 --> 55:51.113
PARIS:
Are the horses ready?

55:51.160 --> 55:55.472
Yes, and the weather's much improved.
Make peace. We're not done here.

55:55.520 --> 55:57.272
HERMIONE:
You're leaving.

55:57.320 --> 55:58.879
I'm afraid so.

55:58.920 --> 56:00.752
When will you return?

56:02.240 --> 56:06.518
My lord, the queen sends her apologies.
She is feeling unwell.

56:06.560 --> 56:07.630
She won't be down to say goodbye.

56:09.320 --> 56:12.039
She is sending a gift for your mother,
Queen Hecuba.

56:13.080 --> 56:15.037
See that it's carefully loaded
onto the ship.

56:20.160 --> 56:21.992
My mother should be here
to bid you farewell.

56:23.320 --> 56:24.594
What does it matter?

56:25.640 --> 56:27.039
Is that why you're leaving early?

56:28.000 --> 56:29.195
Because of her?

56:32.080 --> 56:34.833
She rejected you, didn't she?

56:38.240 --> 56:39.275
Don't come back.

56:55.600 --> 56:56.954
Let's get going.

57:00.440 --> 57:01.510
Let's go!

57:33.400 --> 57:36.995
King Priam seeks your blessing
for this new child.

57:38.160 --> 57:40.197
Oh, gods, be merciful.

58:35.280 --> 58:38.159
Where is my wife?!

58:38.200 --> 58:40.760
I'm not a possession, I'm a woman.

58:40.800 --> 58:42.518
I think, I feel.

58:42.560 --> 58:46.918
What if they come for her?
Agamemnon needs no excuse for a fight.

58:47.520 --> 58:48.715
We are running out of time.

58:48.760 --> 58:51.149
Your wedding will bless
the voyage to Troy.

58:51.200 --> 58:53.350
This doesn't look like a marriage altar.

58:54.560 --> 58:57.313
Last time there was a war here,
I was your age.

58:57.360 --> 59:00.751
WOMAN: / <i>Want your loyalty, Zeus,
to Greece and to me.</i>

59:00.800 --> 59:02.632
This city bows to no one.

59:02.680 --> 59:06.958
We will bring the rage of the gods down
on your Asiatic heads!
